.TH SETUP-LINKS 1 "September 2025" "dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
setup\-links \- manage symlinks for dotfiles configuration using GNU stow
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B setup\-links
[\fB\-u\fR|\fB\-\-unlink\fR \fIpackage\fR...] [\fB\-\-unlink\-all\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates and manages symlinks for dotfiles configuration using GNU stow. By default, creates symlinks for all packages and makes utility scripts globally accessible via ~/.local/bin.
.PP
This script performs the following operations:
.IP \[bu] 2
Automatically cleans up broken symlinks pointing to dotfiles packages
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates necessary XDG directories
.IP \[bu] 2
Links all packages from packages/ directory using stow
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates global symlinks for utility scripts in ~/.local/bin
.IP \[bu] 2
Links manual pages and completions
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-unlink \fIpackage\fR...
Unlink specified packages. Multiple packages can be specified.
.TP
.B \-\-unlink\-all
Unlink all packages and remove all global script symlinks.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.SH DIRECTORIES
The script creates and manages the following directories:
.TP
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Configuration files directory (~/.config by default)
.TP
.B $XDG_STATE_HOME
State files directory (~/.local/state by default)
.TP
.B $XDG_CACHE_HOME
Cache files directory (~/.cache by default)
.TP
.B ~/.ssh
SSH configuration directory (with 700 permissions)
.TP
.B ~/.local/bin
Global script symlinks directory
.SH BACKUP SYSTEM
Before creating symlinks, existing files are automatically backed up to:
.PP
.B ~/.local/state/dotfiles/backup/
.PP
Backup files are named with a timestamp: \fIfilename\fR.YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS
.SH GLOBAL SCRIPT ACCESS
After running setup\-links, utility scripts become globally accessible:
.IP \[bu] 2
update \- System package manager updater
.IP \[bu] 2
setup\-links.sh \- This script (recursive global access)
.IP \[bu] 2
All other scripts from bin/ directory
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B setup\-links
Link all packages and create global script access
.TP
.B setup\-links \-\-unlink vim nvim
Unlink specific packages (vim and nvim)
.TP
.B setup\-links \-\-unlink\-all
Remove all symlinks and global script access
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B DOTFILES_HOME
Path to dotfiles repository (auto-detected)
.TP
.B GHQ_ROOT_PATH
Root path for ghq repositories
.TP
.B GITHUB_USER_NAME
GitHub username for repository path
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.local/state/dotfiles/backup/
Automatic backup directory for replaced files
.TP
.B packages/
Source directory containing stow packages
.TP
.B bin/
Source directory for utility scripts
.SH SAFETY FEATURES
.IP \[bu] 2
Automatic backup of existing files before symlinking
.IP \[bu] 2
Intelligent link detection (skips existing correct links)
.IP \[bu] 2
Broken symlink cleanup specific to dotfiles
.IP \[bu] 2
Safe overwrites with backup
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stow (8),
.BR update (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of personal dotfiles configuration management system.